Preheat your #grill{} to its highest setting. Remove the very top and bottom
from the @aubergine{1} and then slice into 1cm thick discs. Place these on a
#baking tray{}, season with a good pinch of @salt{} and a drizzle of
@oil{}. Rub this into your aubergine slices and then repeat on the other side.
Remove the core from the @red pepper{1}, cut in half lengthways and then slice
each half into three pieces.

Add your pepper to the baking tray with your aubergine and then pop the tray
under the grill. Cook for ~{12-15%minutes}, turning halfway through to make
sure they don't burn.

> You want your pepper and aubergine to be soft and charred at the edges.

When cooked, remove from your grill and sprinkle on the @ground coriander{1.5}.

Keep to one side.

Whilst your aubergine and pepper cooks, get on with the rest of your prep. Cut
the @echalion shallot{1} in half through the root. Peel and then slice into
thin half moon shapes. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1} (or use a
#garlic press{} if you have one). Drain the @mixed beans{1} in a #sieve{}, rinse
under cold water and then keep to one side.

Cut the @British chicken thighs{2} into 2cm chunks. Heat a #saucepan{} over
medium high heat and add a splash of @oil{}. Add your chicken and shallot to
the pan. Cook for ~{5%minutes} until your chicken is browned and your shallot
is soft. Next add your garlic and the @za'atar{1.5} and cook for ~{1%minute}
more.

Add the @tinned plum tomatoes{1} and break them up with a #spoon{}. Stir in the
@chicken stock pot{1} and the @water{200}. Bring to the boil and leave your
sauce to bubble away for ~{10%minutes}, or until it has thickened and reduced
by two-thirds.

As your sauce cooks, keep an eye on your veggies under your grill, and cut the
@goat's cheese{1} into six discs per roll.

When your sauce is nice and thick, stir in your mixed beans. Cook for
~{5%minutes} more. Check your chicken is cooked through (it should no longer be
pink in the middle) and then taste your sauce, add @salt{} and @black pepper{}
if necessary.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Pour your sauce into an #ovenproof dish{}. 

> If the pan is ovenproof, you can use that.

Lay your slices of aubergine and pepper on top of your sauce.

> Aim to cover the beans with your aubergine and pepper slices.

Lay on your goat's cheese, then pop your dish under the grill for
~{3-5%minutes} until your goat's cheese is golden and bubbling. Serve in deep
#bowls{} and enjoy